AB  - As far as I know neither Samuelson nor Merton nor indeed Ophir has challenged the basic principle imbedded in the geometric-mean principle for long-run portfolio selection. If they or he wishes to adopt a significantly different policy and I follow the G policy, in the long run I become3almost certain to have more wealth than they. This hardly seems an erroneous or trivial proposition.
